B) Explain with your own words and in few lines the difference between Angle Modulations and Amplidute Modulations.¶

The difference between Angle modulations and Amplitude modulations is that Angle modulation is used for embedding the baseband message signal in the phase or the frequency of a passband waveform. Amplitude modulations are used for embedding the baseband message signal in the amplitude of a sinusoidal carrier.

The message can be demodulated by using the envelope detector which means that carrier synchronoziation is not needed. If it is about DSB-DC demodulation, then the carrier synchronoziation is needed.
